The paper proposes a deep relational learning framework for learning entity and relationship representations across multiple graphs. This involves knowledge-based inference, which is a key area of research in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed framework uses deep learning techniques, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with constructing a unified graph from multiple incomplete knowledge graphs, which is a problem in database systems (cs.DB). The experiments involve link prediction and entity linkage, which are tasks in natural language processing (cs.CL) and information retrieval (cs.IR), respectively.
